<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Moriendor on 04-09-2002 09:14 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">CDV has updated its press area and ToTheGame has quoted the  [URL=http://www.tothegame.com/article.asp?id=53]press release[/URL] saying that CDV will be showing Divinity at this year's E3 in L.A. The show takes place May, 22-24. Now, usually publishers only present non-released titles at E3. Looks like CDV is not planning on releasing   :div: before E3.
Makes me wonder about CDV's plans in general. The newsletter still says Q2 for the German version and Q3 for the other international versions. I doubt that a publisher like CDV is going to release a game during the holiday season (July/August). We also haven't heard from CDV's Spencer Low in a while. We should expect him to pick up on sending out   :div: features to the press once release is getting closer but CDV is being very silent about   :div: lately.
I get the strange feeling that CDV is not exactly in a hurry to get the game out the door. Maybe one of their marketing gurus has figured out that a fall release would be better in terms of sale figures because people do in general not buy too many games in summer. Who knows? It's just kind of strange that a company remains so silent about a game that is "due for imminent release" as written in the press release.

------------------
Moriendor
Editor @ [URL=http://www.rpgdot.com/]RPGDot[/URL]
Webmaster @ [URL=http://www.divinity-the-sword-of-lies.com]Divinity-The-Sword-Of-Lies.com[/URL]

[This message has been edited by Moriendor (edited 09-04-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
